
GROUP A: Integration Tasks (The EIS Wrappers)
These tasks involve creating the low-level Client/Service methods to communicate with the EIS (Enterprise Integration Service) layer.

Task 1: Implement EIS Consent Read Client
Description: Create a method to check the global consent status from CCMS.

EIS Endpoint: POST /api/consent-core/query/consents/read

Logic: * Map dpCIF to the User's Mobile Number.

Set touchPointId from configuration.

Request Body (from PDF): {"dpCIF": "...", "touchPointId": "...", "dpMobile": "..."}

Response Handling: If status is ACTIVE, return the consentId. If 404/No record, return null.

-------------------------------

Task 2: Implement EIS Consent Write Client
Description: Create a method to push/update consent to CCMS.

EIS Endpoint: POST /api/consent-core/cmd/consents/update

Logic:

Send consentAction as "capture".

Include dpIP (captured from the user's request).

Request Body (from PDF): {"dpCIF": "...", "dpMobile": "...", "touchPointId": "...", "purposeSetId": "...", "consentAction": "capture", "dpIP": "...", "locale": "ENG"}

--------------------------------------

Task 3: Implement EIS Privacy Notice & Purpose Read Clients
Description: Create methods to fetch the latest legal text and purpose metadata.

EIS Endpoints: * Notice: POST /api/consent-core/query/privacy-notice/read

Purpose: POST /api/consent-core/query/purposes/read

Logic: These methods will be used by the scheduler to keep the local privacy_notice_master and purpose_master tables updated.

--------------------------------

GROUP B: Logic & API Tasks (The Core MIF Journey)
These tasks use the methods created in Group A.

Task 4: Consent Evaluation API (POST /evaluate)
Developer Instructions:

Local Check: Query mif_consent_record by mobile number.

External Check: If not found locally, call the EIS Consent Read method (Task 1).

Sync: If the Read API returns an active consent, save it to the local DB immediately with sync_status = 'SYNCED'.

Data Retrieval: If no consent exists anywhere, call the EIS Purpose Read method (Task 3) or fetch from local master tables to provide the pop-up data to the frontend.

Outcome: Returns requiresConsent: true/false + the Notice/Purposes.
----------------------------------------------------

Task 5: Consent Capture API (POST /capture)
Developer Instructions:

Validation: Ensure the user has clicked "Accept".

Local Persistence: Save to mif_consent_record. Set sync_status = 'PENDING'.

Error Handling (Per PDF): If saving to the local SBIePay DB fails, block the process and return the error: "Consent could not be saved. Please try again."

Real-time Push: Attempt to call the EIS Consent Write method (Task 2). If successful, update local sync_status to SYNCED. If it fails or times out, do not block the user; let them proceed to the next MIF step.

-------------------------------------------------
Task 6: ConsentRetryScheduler (Fallback Mechanism)
Developer Instructions:

Query: Find all records in mif_consent_record where sync_status is PENDING or FAILED.

Retry: For each record, call the EIS Consent Write method (Task 2).

Update: On successful 200 OK from EIS, update the local record to SYNCED and store the ccms_consent_id.

Config: Set this to run every 15 minutes via @Scheduled.
-------------------------------------------
Task 7: Master Data Sync Scheduler
Developer Instructions:

Call the EIS Privacy Notice API and EIS Purpose API (Task 3).

Compare the versionId returned by EIS with the one in your local privacy_notice_master.

If a newer version exists, save it and mark it as the active notice for future /evaluate calls.
--------------------------------------------
Task 8: Database Schema & Master Data Setup
Description: As a system, I need a local storage structure to persist consent records and master templates to ensure the MIF journey works even if the central CCMS is down.

Task List:

Create SQL migration scripts for mif_consent_record, privacy_notice_master, and purpose_master.

Implement JPA Entities for all three tables.

Create Basic Repositories (JpaRepository).

Insert initial seed data for the latest Privacy Notice and Purposes provided by the bank.

DB Design Details:

mif_consent_record: mobile_number (Index), mif_id, status (ACTIVE), sync_status (PENDING/SYNCED/FAILED), ccms_consent_id, ip_address, timestamp.




